steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"85iom","text":"For each nucleofection, prepare 20 µl nucleofection solution by mixing 16.4 µl solution I and 3.6 µl supplement. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"clmrl","text":"Re-suspend cell pellets in nucleofection solution. Mix using P1000 or P200 tips to ensure single cell suspension. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"nv4i","text":"Transfer 20 µl cell suspension to the microcentrifuge tube containing the materials to be nucleofected. Mix well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"45s7r","text":"Transfer the entire volume to one cuvette in the 16-cuvette strip. Mark the cuvette used on the lid.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8bkkl","text":"Gently stamp the strip on bench to help the small amount of cell suspension enter the narrow space between the metal paddles properly.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5hhhc","text":"Nucleofect with program, P3 primary cell, CA137","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"620no","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"31hh8","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"64mmk","text":"The Soldner lab has successfully used previous generation Amaxa nucleofection (Nucleofector 2b device, Amaxa Human Stem Cell Nucleofector Kit 2, program B016) for genome editing of hPSCs.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"auh63","text":"After nucleofection, immediately add 150 µl hPSCs medium or feeder-free medium + Rock Inhibitor to the cuvette according to the culturing system that will be used. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8qeb7","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3b9ep","text":"For a detailed description of hPSCs medium, refer to the protocol \"Preparing MEF-cultured hPSCs for nucleofection\" in the collection \"Nucleofection (Amaxa) and electoporation (Biorad) of hPSCs. A link to this collection can be found in the title section of this protocol, located above. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6fm4d","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4ciof","text":"For a detailed description of Feeder-free medium + Rock Inhibitor, refer to the collection \"Feeder-free culturing of hPSCs;\" dx.doi.org/10.17504/protocols.io.b4mcqu2w","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c60lb","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"1n06h","text":"Transfer all cells to a new microcentrifuge tube","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fu39h","text":"Transfer proper amount of cells to MEFs plate or VTN/Matrigel/Geltrex-coated plate","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4cdq1","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e8msj","text":"For a detailed protocol on plating hPSCs on MEFS refer to the collection \"Maintenance and inactivation of mouse embryonic fibroblasts (MEFs) as feeder cells for human pluripotent stem cell culture;\" dx.doi.org/10.17504/protocols.io.b4pbqvin","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a2blo","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4t3jn","text":"For a detailed protocol on coating plates with VTN/Matrigel/Geltrex, refer to the collection \"Feeder-free culturing of hPSCs;\" dx.doi.org/10.17504/protocols.io.b4mcqu2w","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cekg2","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"8ip63","text":"Place the plate in the low oxygen incubator, 3% O2, 5% CO2.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3nbt4","text":"Prepare plasmids, RNA, or RNP as described in their associated protocols in the collection \"Nucleofection (Amaxa) and electroporation (Biorad) of hPSCs.\" A link to this collection can be found in the title section of this protocol, located above. The specific protocol titles for each preparation type are listed below. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6c6u3","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7hn97","text":"Plasmids: Preparing plasmids for nucleofection","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5su5m","text":"RNA: Preparing mRNA for nucleofection","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"epvdj","text":"RNP: In vitro assembling of RNP for nucleofection","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"frceb","text":"Prepare cells for nucleofection as described in protocols  “Preparing MEF-cultured hPSCs for nucleofection” or “Preparing feeder-free hPSCs for nucleofection,\" which are both part of the collection \"Nucleofection (Amaxa) and electroporation (Biorad) of hPSCs.\" A link to this collection can be found in the title section of this protocol, located above","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1qcb","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2n5og","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
